#. <section class="sutta" id="mn102"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn102:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 102"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 102"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn102:0.2"
msgid "Pañcattayasutta"
msgstr "The Five and Three"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn102:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn102:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn102:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn102:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn102:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:2.1"
msgid ""
"“santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino "
"aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhivuttipadāni abhivadanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the "
"future, and assert various hypotheses concerning the future."

msgctxt "mn102:2.2"
msgid "‘Saññī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti—"
msgstr "Some propose this: ‘The self is percipient and is sound after death.’"

msgctxt "mn102:2.3"
msgid "ittheke abhivadanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn102:2.4"
msgid "‘asaññī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Some propose this: ‘The self is non-percipient and is sound after death.’"

msgctxt "mn102:2.5"
msgid "ittheke abhivadanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn102:2.6"
msgid "‘nevasaññīnāsaññī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Some propose this: ‘The self is neither percipient nor non-percipient and is "
"sound after death.’"

msgctxt "mn102:2.7"
msgid "ittheke abhivadanti;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: paññapenti → paññāpenti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn102:2.8"
msgid ""
"sato vā pana sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti, "
"diṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ vā paneke abhivadanti."
msgstr ""
"But some assert the annihilation, eradication, and obliteration of an "
"existing being, while others propose extinguishment in the present life."

msgctxt "mn102:2.9"
msgid ""
"Iti santaṃ vā attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, sato vā pana sattassa "
"ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti, diṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ vā paneke "
"abhivadanti."
msgstr ""
"Thus they assert an existent self that is sound after death; or they assert "
"the annihilation of an existing being; or they propose extinguishment in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "mn102:2.10"
msgid "Iti imāni pañca hutvā tīṇi honti, tīṇi hutvā pañca honti—"
msgstr "In this way five become three, and three become five."

msgctxt "mn102:2.11"
msgid "ayamuddeso pañcattayassa."
msgstr "This is the passage for recitation of the five and three."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.229"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: etaṃ → evaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: paraṃ maraṇā → parammaraṇā (s1-3) | maraṇāti (mr)
#. VAR: panekesaṃ → panetesaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn102:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti "
"arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te "
"bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, "
"ekattasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, nānattasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, parittasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, appamāṇasaññiṃ vā te bhonto "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, etaṃ vā "
"panekesaṃ upātivattataṃ viññāṇakasiṇameke abhivadanti appamāṇaṃ āneñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, the ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is percipient and "
"sound after death describe it as having form, or being formless, or both "
"having form and being formless, or neither having form nor being formless. "
"Or they describe it as of unified perception, or of diverse perception, or "
"of limited perception, or of limitless perception. Or some among those who "
"go beyond this propose universal consciousness, limitless and imperturbable."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. VAR: abhijānāti → pajānāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn102:4.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:4.2"
msgid ""
"Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ "
"maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti "
"arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ "
"attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te bhonto "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, ekattasaññiṃ "
"vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, "
"nānattasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, parittasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, appamāṇasaññiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, yā vā panetāsaṃ saññānaṃ "
"parisuddhā paramā aggā anuttariyā akkhāyati—"
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is percipient and "
"sound after death, describing it as having form, or being formless, or both "
"having form and being formless, or neither having form nor being formless. "
"Or they describe it as of unified perception, or of diverse perception, or "
"of limited perception, or of limitless perception."

msgctxt "mn102:4.3"
msgid ""
"yadi rūpasaññānaṃ yadi arūpasaññānaṃ yadi ekattasaññānaṃ yadi "
"nānattasaññānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn102:4.4"
msgid "‘Natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanameke abhivadanti appamāṇaṃ āneñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Or some, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, propose the dimension of "
"nothingness, limitless and imperturbable. They declare that this is the "
"purest, highest, best, and supreme of all those perceptions, whether of form "
"or of formlessness or of unity or of diversity."

# The phrasing here is a little odd. But I can't see a justification for the way BB has construed the syntax.
msgctxt "mn102:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:4.6"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding thus and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.231"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti "
"arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te "
"bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā."
msgstr ""
"Now, the ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is non-percipient and "
"sound after death describe it as having form, or being formless, or both "
"having form and being formless, or neither having form nor being formless."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā tesamete paṭikkosanti."
msgstr ""
"So they reject those who assert a self that is percipient and sound after "
"death."

msgctxt "mn102:6.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn102:6.3"
msgid ""
"Saññā rogo saññā gaṇḍo saññā sallaṃ, etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ: "
"‘asaññan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Because they believe that perception is a disease, a boil, a dart, and that "
"the state of non-perception is peaceful and sublime."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:7.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti "
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:7.2"
msgid ""
"ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ "
"maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti "
"arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ "
"attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te bhonto "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā."
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is non-percipient and "
"sound after death, describing it as having form, or being formless, or both "
"having form and being formless, or neither having form nor being formless."

msgctxt "mn102:7.3"
msgid "Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "But if any ascetic or brahmin should say this:"

#. VAR: saṅkhārehi, viññāṇassa → aññatra viññāṇā (s1-3, km) | aññatra viññāṇassa (pts1) | aññatra viññāṇena (mr)
msgctxt "mn102:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahamaññatra rūpā, aññatra vedanāya, aññatra saññāya, aññatra saṅkhārehi, "
"viññāṇassa āgatiṃ vā gatiṃ vā cutiṃ vā upapattiṃ vā vuddhiṃ vā virūḷhiṃ vā "
"vepullaṃ vā paññapessāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Apart from form, feeling, perception, and choices, I will describe the "
"coming and going of consciousness, its passing away and reappearing, its "
"growth, increase, and maturity.’"

msgctxt "mn102:7.5"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr "That is not possible."

msgctxt "mn102:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:7.7"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti "
"arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ "
"attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca "
"vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā."
msgstr ""
"Now, the ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is neither percipient "
"nor non-percipient and sound after death describe it as having form, or "
"being formless, or both having form and being formless, or neither having "
"form nor being formless."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā tesamete paṭikkosanti, yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ "
"attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā tesamete paṭikkosanti."
msgstr ""
"So they reject those who assert a self that is percipient and sound after "
"death, as well as those who assert a self that is non-percipient and sound "
"after death."

msgctxt "mn102:9.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn102:9.3"
msgid ""
"Saññā rogo saññā gaṇḍo saññā sallaṃ, asaññā sammoho, etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ "
"paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Because they believe that perception is a disease, a boil, a dart, and that "
"the state of neither perception nor non-perception is peaceful and sublime."

msgctxt "mn102:9.4"
msgid "‘nevasaññānāsaññan’ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:10.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:10.2"
msgid ""
"Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, arūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā, rūpiñca arūpiñca "
"vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ "
"paraṃ maraṇā, nevarūpiṃ nārūpiṃ vā te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā."
msgstr ""
"There are ascetics and brahmins who assert a self that is neither percipient "
"nor non-percipient and sound after death, describing it as having form, or "
"being formless, or both having form and being formless, or neither having "
"form nor being formless."

# Cp. SN 35.95
#. VAR: bhikkhave, akkhāyati → āyata­na­mak­khā­yati (mr)
msgctxt "mn102:10.3"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā "
"diṭṭhasutamutaviññātabbasaṅkhāramattena etassa āyatanassa upasampadaṃ "
"paññapenti, byasanañhetaṃ, bhikkhave, akkhāyati etassa āyatanassa "
"upasampadāya."
msgstr ""
"Some ascetics or brahmins assert the attainment of that dimension merely "
"through the conditioned phenomena of what is seen, heard, thought, and "
"known. But that is said to be a disastrous approach."

# Cp SN 14.11
msgctxt "mn102:10.4"
msgid "Na hetaṃ, bhikkhave, āyatanaṃ saṅkhārasamāpattipattabbamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"For that dimension is said to be not attainable by means of conditioned "
"phenomena,"

msgctxt "mn102:10.5"
msgid "saṅkhārāvasesasamāpattipattabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, āyatanamakkhāyati."
msgstr "but only with a residue of conditioned phenomena."

msgctxt "mn102:10.6"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:10.7"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:11.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ "
"vibhavaṃ paññapenti, tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā saññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā tesamete paṭikkosanti, yepi te bhonto "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā asaññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā tesamete "
"paṭikkosanti, yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā nevasaññīnāsaññiṃ attānaṃ "
"paññapenti arogaṃ paraṃ maraṇā tesamete paṭikkosanti."
msgstr ""
"Now, the ascetics and brahmins who assert the annihilation, eradication, and "
"obliteration of an existing being reject those who assert a self that is "
"sound after death, whether percipient or non-percipient or neither "
"percipient non-percipient."

msgctxt "mn102:11.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

# BB has “rushing onward” for uddham saram, while Hornner has loftily maintain attachment. But it seems to me the point is related to the common phrase uddhamsoto, i.e. heading upstream, i.e. getting reborn in a higher realm.
#. VAR: uddhaṃ saraṃ → uddhaṃsarā (bj, pts1) | uddhaṃ parāmasanti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn102:11.3"
msgid "Sabbepime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhaṃ saraṃ āsattiṃyeva abhivadanti:"
msgstr ""
"Because all of those ascetics and brahmins only assert their attachment to "
"moving up to a higher realm:"

msgctxt "mn102:11.4"
msgid "‘iti pecca bhavissāma, iti pecca bhavissāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘After death we shall be like this! After death we shall be like that!’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:12.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma vāṇijassa vāṇijjāya gacchato evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Suppose a trader was going to market, thinking:"

msgctxt "mn102:12.2"
msgid "‘ito me idaṃ bhavissati, iminā idaṃ lacchāmī’ti;"
msgstr "‘With this, that shall be mine! This way, I shall get that!’"

msgctxt "mn102:12.3"
msgid "evamevime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā vāṇijūpamā maññe paṭibhanti:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, those ascetics and brahmins seem to be like traders when "
"they say:"

msgctxt "mn102:12.4"
msgid "‘iti pecca bhavissāma, iti pecca bhavissāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘After death we shall be like this! After death we shall be like that!’"

msgctxt "mn102:12.5"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:12.6"
msgid ""
"Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ "
"paññapenti te sakkāyabhayā sakkāyaparijegucchā sakkāyaññeva anuparidhāvanti "
"anuparivattanti."
msgstr ""
"The ascetics and brahmins who assert the annihilation, eradication, and "
"obliteration of an existing being; from fear and disgust with identity, they "
"just keep running and circling around identity."

#. VAR: khile → khīle (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn102:12.7"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma sā gaddulabaddho daḷhe thambhe vā khile vā upanibaddho, "
"tameva thambhaṃ vā khilaṃ vā anuparidhāvati anuparivattati;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose a dog on a leash was tethered to a strong post or pillar. It would "
"just keeping running and circling around that post or pillar."

msgctxt "mn102:12.8"
msgid ""
"evamevime bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā sakkāyabhayā sakkāyaparijegucchā "
"sakkāyaññeva anuparidhāvanti anuparivattanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, those ascetics and brahmins, from fear and disgust with "
"identity, just keep running and circling around identity."

msgctxt "mn102:12.9"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:12.10"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:13.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aparantakappikā "
"aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhivuttipadāni "
"abhivadanti, sabbe te imāneva pañcāyatanāni abhivadanti etesaṃ vā aññataraṃ."
msgstr ""
"Whatever ascetics and brahmins theorize about the future, and propose "
"various hypotheses concerning the future, all of them propose one or other "
"of these five theses."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.234"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:14.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino "
"pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhivuttipadāni abhivadanti."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past, and "
"propose various hypotheses concerning the past. They propose the following, "
"each insisting that theirs is the only truth and that everything else is "
"wrong."

msgctxt "mn102:14.2"
msgid "‘Sassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are eternal.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.3"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘asassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are not eternal.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.4"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘sassato ca asassato ca attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are both eternal and not eternal.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.5"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘nevasassato nāsassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are neither eternal nor not eternal.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.6"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘antavā attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are finite.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.7"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘anantavā attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are infinite.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.8"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘antavā ca anantavā ca attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are both finite and infinite.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.9"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘nevantavā nānantavā attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are neither finite nor infinite.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.10"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘ekattasaññī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are unified in perception.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.11"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘nānattasaññī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos are diverse in perception.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.12"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘parittasaññī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos have limited perception.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.13"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘appamāṇasaññī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos have limitless perception.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.14"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘ekantasukhī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos experience nothing but happiness.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.15"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘ekantadukkhī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos experience nothing but suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.16"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘sukhadukkhī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos experience both happiness and suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.17"
msgid ""
"ittheke abhivadanti, ‘adukkhamasukhī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ "
"moghamaññan’ti—"
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos experience neither happiness nor suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn102:14.18"
msgid "ittheke abhivadanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:15.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Now, consider the ascetics and brahmins whose view is as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:15.2"
msgid ""
"‘sassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti, tesaṃ vata "
"aññatreva saddhāya aññatra ruciyā aññatra anussavā aññatra ākāraparivitakkā "
"aññatra diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ bhavissati parisuddhaṃ "
"pariyodātanti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal. This is the only truth, other ideas "
"are stupid.’ It’s simply not possible for them to have purified and clear "
"personal knowledge of this, apart from faith, personal preference, oral "
"tradition, reasoned contemplation, or acceptance of a view after "
"consideration."

#. VAR: yadapi → yadipi (mr)
msgctxt "mn102:15.3"
msgid ""
"Paccattaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, ñāṇe asati parisuddhe pariyodāte yadapi te "
"bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā tattha ñāṇabhāgamattameva pariyodapenti tadapi tesaṃ "
"bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upādānamakkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"And in the absence of such knowledge, even the partial knowledge that they "
"are clear about is said to be grasping on their part."

msgctxt "mn102:15.4"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:15.5"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
