msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Now, consider the ascetics and brahmins whose view is is follows."

msgctxt "mn102:16.2"
msgid "‘asassato attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññan’ti … pe …"
msgstr "The self and the cosmos are not eternal,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.3"
msgid "sassato ca asassato ca attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or both eternal and not eternal,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.4"
msgid "nevasassato nāsassato attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or neither eternal nor not-eternal,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.5"
msgid "antavā attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or finite,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.6"
msgid "anantavā attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or infinite,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.7"
msgid "antavā ca anantavā ca attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or both finite and infinite,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.8"
msgid "nevantavā nānantavā attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or neither infinite or infinite,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.9"
msgid "ekattasaññī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or of unified perception,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.10"
msgid "nānattasaññī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or of diverse perception,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.11"
msgid "parittasaññī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or of limited perception,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.12"
msgid "appamāṇasaññī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or of limitless perception,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.13"
msgid "ekantasukhī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or experience nothing but happiness,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.14"
msgid "ekantadukkhī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or experience nothing but suffering,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.15"
msgid "sukhadukkhī attā ca loko ca …"
msgstr "or experience both happiness and suffering,"

msgctxt "mn102:16.16"
msgid ""
"adukkhamasukhī attā ca loko ca, idameva saccaṃ moghamaññanti, tesaṃ vata "
"aññatreva saddhāya aññatra ruciyā aññatra anussavā aññatra ākāraparivitakkā "
"aññatra diṭṭhinijjhānakkhantiyā paccattaṃyeva ñāṇaṃ bhavissati parisuddhaṃ "
"pariyodātanti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"or experience neither happiness nor suffering. It’s simply not possible for "
"them to have purified and clear personal knowledge of this, apart from "
"faith, personal preference, oral tradition, reasoned contemplation, or "
"acceptance of a view after consideration."

msgctxt "mn102:16.17"
msgid ""
"Paccattaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, ñāṇe asati parisuddhe pariyodāte yadapi te "
"bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā tattha ñāṇabhāgamattameva pariyodapenti tadapi tesaṃ "
"bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ upādānamakkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"And in the absence of such knowledge, even the partial knowledge that they "
"are clear about is said to be grasping on their part."

msgctxt "mn102:16.18"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:16.19"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:17.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca "
"paṭinissaggā, aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ "
"anadhiṭṭhānā, pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati:"
msgstr ""
"Now, some ascetics and brahmins, letting go of theories about the past and "
"the future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, enter and remain in the "
"rapture of seclusion:"

msgctxt "mn102:17.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in the "
"rapture of seclusion.’"

msgctxt "mn102:17.3"
msgid "Tassa sā pavivekā pīti nirujjhati."
msgstr "But that rapture of seclusion of theirs ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:17.4"
msgid ""
"Pavivekāya pītiyā nirodhā uppajjati domanassaṃ, domanassassa nirodhā "
"uppajjati pavivekā pīti."
msgstr ""
"When the rapture of seclusion ceases, sadness arises; and when sadness "
"ceases, the rapture of seclusion arises."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:18.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yaṃ chāyā jahati taṃ ātapo pharati, yaṃ ātapo jahati "
"taṃ chāyā pharati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how the sunlight fills the space when the shadow leaves, or the "
"shadow fills the space when the sunshine leaves."

msgctxt "mn102:18.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, pavivekāya pītiyā nirodhā uppajjati domanassaṃ, "
"domanassassa nirodhā uppajjati pavivekā pīti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the rapture of seclusion ceases, sadness arises; and "
"when sadness ceases, the rapture of seclusion arises."

msgctxt "mn102:18.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:18.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, "
"aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ anadhiṭṭhānā, "
"pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharati:"
msgstr ""
"This good ascetic or brahmin, letting go of theories about the past and the "
"future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, enters and remains in the "
"rapture of seclusion:"

msgctxt "mn102:18.5"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ pavivekaṃ pītiṃ upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in the "
"rapture of seclusion.’"

msgctxt "mn102:18.6"
msgid "Tassa sā pavivekā pīti nirujjhati."
msgstr "But that rapture of seclusion of theirs ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:18.7"
msgid ""
"Pavivekāya pītiyā nirodhā uppajjati domanassaṃ, domanassassa nirodhā "
"uppajjati pavivekā pīti."
msgstr ""
"When the rapture of seclusion ceases, sadness arises; and when sadness "
"ceases, the rapture of seclusion arises."

msgctxt "mn102:18.8"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:18.9"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.236"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:19.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca "
"paṭinissaggā, aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ "
"anadhiṭṭhānā, pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati:"
msgstr ""
"Now, some ascetics and brahmins, letting go of theories about the past and "
"the future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, going beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion, enter and remain in spiritual bliss."

msgctxt "mn102:19.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in "
"spiritual bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn102:19.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ nirujjhati."
msgstr "But that spiritual bliss of theirs ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:19.4"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisassa sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati pavivekā pīti, pavivekāya pītiyā "
"nirodhā uppajjati nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When spiritual bliss ceases, the rapture of seclusion arises; and when the "
"rapture of seclusion ceases, spiritual bliss arises."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:20.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yaṃ chāyā jahati taṃ ātapo pharati, yaṃ ātapo jahati "
"taṃ chāyā pharati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how the sunlight fills the space when the shadow leaves, or the "
"shadow fills the space when the sunshine leaves. …"

msgctxt "mn102:20.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, nirāmisassa sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati pavivekā "
"pīti, pavivekāya pītiyā nirodhā uppajjati nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn102:20.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:20.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, "
"aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ anadhiṭṭhānā, "
"pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā, nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ upasampajja viharati:"
msgstr ""
"This good ascetic or brahmin, letting go of theories about the past and the "
"future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, going beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion, enters and remains in spiritual bliss."

msgctxt "mn102:20.5"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ upasampajja viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in "
"spiritual bliss.’"

msgctxt "mn102:20.6"
msgid "Tassa taṃ nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ nirujjhati."
msgstr "But that spiritual bliss of theirs ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:20.7"
msgid ""
"Nirāmisassa sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati pavivekā pīti, pavivekāya pītiyā "
"nirodhā uppajjati nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When spiritual bliss ceases, the rapture of seclusion arises; and when the "
"rapture of seclusion ceases, spiritual bliss arises."

msgctxt "mn102:20.8"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:20.9"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.237"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:21.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca "
"paṭinissaggā, aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ "
"anadhiṭṭhānā, pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā, nirāmisassa sukhassa "
"samatikkamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharati:"
msgstr ""
"Now, some ascetics and brahmins, letting go of theories about the past and "
"the future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, going beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion and spiritual bliss, enter and remain in neutral feeling."

msgctxt "mn102:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in "
"neutral feeling.’"

msgctxt "mn102:21.3"
msgid "Tassa sā adukkhamasukhā vedanā nirujjhati."
msgstr "Then that neutral feeling ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:21.4"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ, nirāmisassa "
"sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"When neutral feeling ceases, spiritual bliss arises; and when spiritual "
"bliss ceases, neutral feelings arises."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:22.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yaṃ chāyā jahati taṃ ātapo pharati, yaṃ ātapo jahati "
"taṃ chāyā pharati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like how the sunlight fills the space when the shadow leaves, or the "
"shadow fills the space when the sunshine leaves. …"

msgctxt "mn102:22.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati "
"nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ, nirāmisassa sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati adukkhamasukhā "
"vedanā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn102:22.3"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:22.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, "
"aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ anadhiṭṭhānā, "
"pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā, nirāmisassa sukhassa samatikkamā, "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja viharati:"
msgstr ""
"This good ascetic or brahmin, letting go of theories about the past and the "
"future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, going beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion and spiritual bliss, enters and remains in neutral feeling."

msgctxt "mn102:22.5"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ adukkhamasukhaṃ vedanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful, this is sublime, that is, entering and remaining in "
"neutral feeling.’"

msgctxt "mn102:22.6"
msgid "Tassa sā adukkhamasukhā vedanā nirujjhati."
msgstr "Then that neutral feeling ceases."

msgctxt "mn102:22.7"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya nirodhā uppajjati nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ, nirāmisassa "
"sukhassa nirodhā uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"When neutral feeling ceases, spiritual bliss arises; and when spiritual "
"bliss ceases, neutral feelings arises."

msgctxt "mn102:22.8"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:22.9"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:23.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca "
"paṭinissaggā, aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ "
"anadhiṭṭhānā, pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā, nirāmisassa sukhassa "
"samatikkamā, adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya samatikkamā:"
msgstr ""
"Now, some ascetics and brahmins, letting go of theories about the past and "
"the future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, go beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion, spiritual bliss, and neutral feeling."

msgctxt "mn102:23.2"
msgid "‘santohamasmi, nibbutohamasmi, anupādānohamasmī’ti samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"They regard themselves like this: ‘I am at peace; I am extinguished; I am "
"free of grasping.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:24.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato abhijānāti."
msgstr "The Realized One understands this as follows."

msgctxt "mn102:24.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, "
"aparantānudiṭṭhīnañca paṭinissaggā, sabbaso kāmasaṃyojanānaṃ anadhiṭṭhānā, "
"pavivekāya pītiyā samatikkamā, nirāmisassa sukhassa samatikkamā, "
"adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya samatikkamā:"
msgstr ""
"This good ascetic or brahmin, letting go of theories about the past and the "
"future, shedding the fetters of sensuality, goes beyond the rapture of "
"seclusion, spiritual bliss, and neutral feeling."

msgctxt "mn102:24.3"
msgid "‘santohamasmi, nibbutohamasmi, anupādānohamasmī’ti samanupassati;"
msgstr ""
"They regard themselves like this: ‘I am at peace; I am extinguished; I am "
"free of grasping.’"

msgctxt "mn102:24.4"
msgid "addhā ayamāyasmā nibbānasappāyaṃyeva paṭipadaṃ abhivadati."
msgstr ""
"Clearly this venerable speaks of a practice that’s conducive to "
"extinguishment."

msgctxt "mn102:24.5"
msgid ""
"Atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā pubbantānudiṭṭhiṃ vā "
"upādiyamāno upādiyati, aparantānudiṭṭhiṃ vā upādiyamāno upādiyati, "
"kāmasaṃyojanaṃ vā upādiyamāno upādiyati, pavivekaṃ vā pītiṃ upādiyamāno "
"upādiyati, nirāmisaṃ vā sukhaṃ upādiyamāno upādiyati, adukkhamasukhaṃ vā "
"vedanaṃ upādiyamāno upādiyati."
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, they still grasp at theories about the past or the future, or "
"the fetters of sensuality, or the rapture of seclusion, or spiritual bliss, "
"or neutral feeling."

msgctxt "mn102:24.6"
msgid "Yañca kho ayamāyasmā:"
msgstr "And when they regard themselves like this:"

msgctxt "mn102:24.7"
msgid ""
"‘santohamasmi, nibbutohamasmi, anupādānohamasmī’ti samanupassati tadapi "
"imassa bhoto samaṇassa brāhmaṇassa upādānamakkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"‘I am at peace; I am extinguished; I am free of grasping,’ that’s also said "
"to be grasping on their part."

msgctxt "mn102:24.8"
msgid ""
"‘Tayidaṃ saṅkhataṃ oḷārikaṃ atthi kho pana saṅkhārānaṃ nirodho atthetan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘All that is conditioned and coarse. But there is the cessation of "
"conditions—<em>that</em> is real.’"

msgctxt "mn102:24.9"
msgid "iti viditvā tassa nissaraṇadassāvī tathāgato tadupātivatto."
msgstr ""
"Understanding this and seeing the escape from it, the Realized One has gone "
"beyond all that."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:25.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, tathāgatena anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ "
"abhisambuddhaṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"But the Realized One has awakened to the supreme state of sublime peace, "
"that is,"

msgctxt "mn102:25.2"
msgid ""
"channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca "
"nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimokkho”ti."
msgstr ""
"liberation by not grasping after truly understanding these six sense fields’ "
"origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.238"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn102:25.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn102:25.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn102:25.5"
msgid "Pañcattayasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
